The paper is about computational problems in cooperative games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also incorporates complexity measures and analyzes the computational complexity of various solution concepts, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses efficient algorithms for special classes of games, which could fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
